<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gunshots Interrupt Revolution Anniversary Ceremonies </TI></H3>
<H4>   Khamene'i Attends Celebrations </H4>
<F P=102> LD0102111394 Tehran IRNA in English 1014 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 1, IRNA -- Leader of the Islamic 
revolution Ayatollah 'Ali Khamene'i on Tuesday [1 February] 
attended the shrine of the late founder of the Islamic Republic 
Imam Khomeyni to mark the beginning of the ten-day dawn 
(February 1-11) ceremonies. 
  The ceremonies are held on the occasion of the 15th 
anniversary of the victory of the 1979 Islamic revolution. 
  After attending the shrine of the late Imam Khomeyni, the 
leader visited the martyrs quarter of Behesht-e Zahra cemetery 
and paid homage to the martyrs of the revolution and those of 
the imposed war. 

</TEXT>

