<H3> <TI>   $10.7 Billion Oil Revenue Budgeted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101101694 Tehran IRNA in English 0747 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3101101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 31, IRNA -- The country's overall oil 
revenue in the next year's budget bill was set at rls. 
17,651,988,000,000 or dlrs. 10,721,300,000 by the deputies in 
the Majlis open session Sunday. Deliberations on 1373 (starting 
March 21) budget bill began Saturday and its outline was 
approved yesterday. Discussion on other sources of the 
government revenue still continues in the Majlis. 

