<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Price Increases on Oil Rejected </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101110294 Tehran IRNA in English 1010 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3101110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 31, IRNA -- Increase in prices of 
natural gas, gasoline, kerosene, gas oil and fuel oil, predicted 
in the next year budget bill, was voted down by the Majles 
deputies Monday. 
  In its open session today, the Majles deliberating the 1373 
(starting March 21) budget bill, did not approve the paragraph 
(a) of the note 25 of the proposed bill. 
  The paragraph had envisaged that prices of each liter of 
gasoline, kerosene, gas oil and fuel oil were to increase to 
rls. 80, 20, 15 and 10 respectively and each cubic meter of gas 
to rls. 12.4. 
  After the proposed amendments for the paragraph were not 
approved, the paragraph itself was voted down by the deputies. 
  According to the rules, when the draft of an article is not 
approved, the Majles votes for its elimination. 
  In continuation of the session, the Majles voted for 
elimination of the paragraph (a) of the note 25. 
  In its open session last night, the Majles voted down the 
elimination of the note 25 and then paragraph (a) of the note. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

