<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Algerian Leader Urged To Free Madani, Belhadj </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102113494 Tehran IRNA in English 1045 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 1, IRNA -- The daily `TEHRAN TIMES' 
Tuesday recommended the newly-selected Algerian president to 
unconditionally release Abassi Madani and Ali Belhadj if he 
wishes to show sincerity regarding a national reconciliation. 
  General Liamine Zeroual was selected by the Algerian High 
Security Council as the new president Sunday. 
  The English daily said that Zeroual enjoys a good reputation 
compared to the five members of the current unelected collective 
presidency. "Nevertheless, his presidency cannot bring 
legitimacy to the Algerian regime." 
  Noting that the Algerian problem is of a politico-military 
nature, the editorial said "Algeria's efforts to destroy its 
domestic opposition and to accuse other countries of interfering 
in its internal affairs have met with failure. 
  "If Zeroual truly wants a national reconciliation...He 
should 
realize that his time to legitimize his own presidency and the 
Algerian Goverment is limited. 
  The process of legitimization must take place soon or the 
current conflict would blow up into a full-fledged civil war, 
the daily added. 
  "This legitimacy must be approved by the people of Algeria, 
not by Paris or Washington," wrote the editorial. 

</TEXT>

