<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Leaders View Zeroual Appointment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101150494 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3101150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] We have met with a number of 
guests and recorded their reaction to the appointment of Liamine 
Zeroual as head of state, on the sidelines of the swearing-in 
ceremony. Their reaction was as follows: 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified speaker] We are expecting 
things to start to happen after this appointment. What is 
important today is what the man of the transitional period will 
do rather than who is in charge of the transitional period. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Kamel Laroussi, you are a 
leading member of the Islamic Nahda Movement. What is your 
reaction? 
  [Laroussi] In the name of God, the merciful, the 
compassionate. The leader of the movement already answered this 
question when he said that the appointment of Liamine Zeroual to 
lead the country during this period came about first because he 
was a member of the National Liberation Army. However, what we 
are hoping will take place during the next phase is that he will 
work in accordance with the consensus reached by the parties, in 
a bid to bring about national reconciliation. Thank you. 
  [Correspondent] Ahmed Mahsas is a historic figure and at the 
same time he is leader of the Union of Democratic Forces. Mr. 
Mahsas, what is your reaction to the appointment of Liamine 
Zeroual as head of state? 
  [Mahsas] Of course we, as a political movement, did not take 
part in the dialogue for certain reasons. However, as far as 
state issues are concerned our concern is to correct the 
foundations of the state. We believe that the appointment of 
brother Liamine Zeroual is a positive move in this decisive 
period. He has shouldered a colossal responsibility. Such an 
appointment may be able to stop the serious deterioration if 
measures are taken that will make the Algerian people feel that 
something new is taking place. [passage omitted] 
  [Correspondent] Thank you, Mr. Mahsas. Mr. Abdelkader 
Merbah, leader of the Majd party, will you give us your reaction 
to the appointment of Liamine Zeroual as head of state? 
  [Merbah] I said in my news conference on 23 December that 
there were some signs for a positive change. I was then trying 
to hint to Liamine Zeroual as well as other officials of the 
state. Thanks be to God, time has shown that I was right. We 
are very happy at the appointment of Liamine Zeroual as head of 
state because we think he is committed to making a clean break 
with the past, and he is a fair and strong man. A strong 
Algeria needs strong men to set the house in order. Algerians 
were desperate. We hope that our despair is over with the 
appointment of men like Zeroual to lead the country. [passage 
omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

