<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Terrorists' Shot Dead; Imam Arrested </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101224494 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in French 1800 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3101224494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [words indistinct] terrorists were shot dead by the 
police between Thursday and Saturday in the province of Blida, 
Algiers, and Bouira. [Name indistinct] reports: 
  [Reporter] According to the security forces, one terrorist 
was shot dead on Thursday in Amrossa, in the province of Blida, 
after he opened fire on the police from a mosque where he had 
taken refuge. 
  Another terrorist was also shot dead in the district of 
Gourouba in Algiers. He was wanted for various crimes. An 
automatic pistol with a magazine and ammunition were found on 
him. 
  Two other terrorists, who were also wanted, were shot dead 
on 
Saturday in the Casbah. An automatic pistol with a magazine, 
ammunition, and a professional identity card which had belonged 
to a policeman were found on him. 
  On Saturday, in Lakhdaria, one terrorist was shot dead 
during 
a search operation. 
  In Kouba, one 23-year-old man was arrested. He was the imam 
at the Benhaddad Mosque in Kouba. After appearing before the 
court for sending death threats, he was remanded in custody. 
  And finally, in Laghouat, one terrorist was wounded and 
arrested at around 0130 on Sunday as he was attempting to set 
fire to the post office. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

