<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Tours Kashmir Areas as Rao Reviews Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2901091094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0435 
GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2901091094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister held an urgent meeting with the 
home minister in New Delhi yesterday. Mr. S.B. Chavan, who was 
in Chandigarh, rushed to Delhi for the talks. Agency reports 
say that the law and order situation in the Kashmir Valley 
figured prominently in their talks. The minister of state for 
home affairs, Mr. Rajesh Pilot, and several senior officials of 
the Home Ministry were present at the meeting. The prime 
minister is understood to have given some new directions to deal 
with the situation. 
  Later, Mr. Chavan left for Jammu where he has held detailed 
discussions with the state governor, General K.V. Krishna Rao, 
on the situation in Jammu and Kashmir. The governor apprised 
him of the steps initiated to achieve the objective of bringing 
normalcy and an elected government in the state. Mr. Chavan 
also had a meeting with the four advisers to the governor and 
the state chief secretary. The home minister will address 
senior officials of the state government today and also take 
stock of the implementation of development schemes. He is to 
visit some of the migrants' camps in Jammu. Mr. Chavan will 
visit Doda and Kishtwar tomorrow for an on-the-spot study of the 
situation. 

</TEXT>

