<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Denies Shooting Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101150994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3101150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An official spokesman today strongly refuted press 
reports that the union home minister's helicopter was fired at 
during his visit to Doda yesterday. The spokesman said that no 
such incident concerning the home minister's helicopter took 
place during his visit to Doda and Kishtwar yesterday. However, 
militants fired a few rounds from a very distant place from Doda 
town, which were not aimed at the helicopter or any particular 
object. Moreover, the home minister's helicopter landed much 
later than this random firing. 

</TEXT>

