<H3> <TI>   Pakistani Troops Fire Rockets at Punch District </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2901084094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0435 
GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2901084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistani troops again fired six rockets from 
across the border in Mendhar Sector of Punch District in Jammu 
and Kashmir yesterday. No damage is reported. According to 
official sources, Pakistani troops have been firing rockets on 
the Indian side without any provocation for the last four days. 
  The president of the All-India Youth Congress-I, Mr. 
Maninderjit Singh Bitta, has said that Youth Congress-I 
activists will demonstrate near the Indo-Pakistan border at 
Atari on the fifth of next month. Addressing a rally in 
Bhubaneswar, he said this is to rebuff the three-day strike call 
given by Pakistan Premier Ms. Benazir Bhutto in that country on 
the Kashmir issue. 

</TEXT>

