<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rapid Action Force Deployed in Kanpur After Violence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2901090094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2901090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The situation in the curfew-bound areas of Kanpur 
in Uttar Pradesh is under control. The state inspector general 
of police told our Kanpur correspondent that there has been no 
report of any untoward incident since last evening. The 
Anwarganj police station in charge has been suspended. CRPF 
[Central Reserve Police Force] and Rapid Action Force jawans 
[soldiers] have been deployed in the curfew-bound areas. No 
arrest has so far been made in connection with yesterday's 
violent incidents. As reported, eight people were injured in 
these incidents in Anwarganj area and curfew was imposed in the 
entire area between Mulganj crossing to Bansmandi. 

</TEXT>

