<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Antitank Missile Passes Flight Test </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101125694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3101125694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The most modern antitank missile, Nag [Cobra], has 
been successfully flight tested. Developed by the Defense 
Research and Development Organization, DRDO, it is a 
third-generation missile with a range of 4 km and is capable of 
destroying armor. A Defense Ministry release in New Delhi says 
four test-flights of Nag were successfully conducted for two 
days on Saturday and Sunday. A missile carrier truck vehicle 
was used for carrying out these tests. India is one of the three 
countries which are developing this class of advanced missiles. 

</TEXT>

