<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   50th Session of UN Human Rights Commission Opens </TI></H3>
<H4>   'Arafat: Withdrawal Delay Threatens Peace </H4>
<F P=102> LD0102153994 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 1500 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Palestine Liberation Organization leader 
Yasir 'Arafat has warned that further delays in the withdrawal 
of Israeli troops from the occupied territories could threaten 
the whole Middle East peace process. Mr. 'Arafat told a news 
conference in Geneva that Israel had asked for six days to 
review a weekend agreement reached with the Israeli Foreign 
Minister Shim'on Peres in the Swiss resort of Davos. He was 
speaking shortly after giving a speech to the UN Human Rights 
Commission, in which he said Palestinians still faced abuses in 
the occupied territories. The PLO leader said he still hoped 
the agreement on implementing Palestinian self-rule could be 
signed next week when he meets Mr. Peres in the Egyptian 
capital, Cairo. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

