<H3> <TI>   Sha'th: No Date for Further PLO-Israeli Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0202112694 Paris AFP in English 1052 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0202112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, Feb 2 (AFP) -- Israeli and PLO negotiators 
have not yet set a date for further talks on Palestinian 
autonomy, PLO chief negotiator Nabil Sha'th said here Wednesday 
[2 February]. 
  Sha'th denied an earlier Israeli television report that 
talks 
would resume in Cairo Wednesday. 
  The two sides are due to meet again to finalise an accord on 
launching Palestinian self-rule in the Gaza Strip and Jericho, 
following the meeting in Davos, Switzerland, last weekend 
between PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres. 

</TEXT>

