<H3> <TI>   Economic Commission With Canada Concludes Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101202794 Riyadh SPA in English 1927 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3101202794 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, Jan 31, SPA -- The joint Saudi-Canadian 
Commission on Economic and Technical Cooperation concluded here 
today its meetings under the co-chairmanship of Saudi Acting 
Foreign Under Secretary for Economic and Cultural Affairs 
Mohammad Mamoun Kurdi and the Canadian Foreign Under Secretary 
for International Trade Allen Kilpatrick. 
  Addressing the final session, Kurdi expressed thanks and 
appreciation for the spirit of cordiality and cooperation which 
prevailed during the commission's deliberations. 
  He stressed that the joint goal of the Saudi and Canadian 
sides is to boost bilateral cooperation and expressed hope that 
the outcome of the meetings would contribute to realizing more 
progress for the two countries. 
  Kilpatrick praised Saudi-Canadian trade relations and 
pointed 
to the increase of joint ventures and investments. 

</TEXT>

