<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Approves Bill on Redivision of States </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0102164594 Khartoum SUNA in English 0929 GMT 01 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0102164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 1 Feb (SUNA) -- The Transitional National 
Assembly (TNA), chaired by Muhammad al-Amin Khalifah, Monday 
approved the bill on the tenth constitutional decree on the 
states' redivision for 1994 at the second reading stage. 
  The decree, which stipulates increasing the number of states 
in the Sudan to 26 states, was approved by TNA at the second 
reading stage in accordance with a report presented to the 
assembly by the legal affairs and decentralization committees. 
  A number of MPs spoke at the session, expressing their 
unanimous support for the decree, which they affirm has come to 
fulfill the desires of the Sudanese masses. 

</TEXT>

