<H3> <TI>   `Arafat Remarks on Confederation Draw Reaction </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-Husayni Clarifies 'Arafat's Position </H4>
<F P=102> TA0202061894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT 2 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0202061894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Faysal al-Husayni, one of the leaders of the 
Palestinians in the territories, said that when Yasir 'Arafat 
told Shim'on Peres that he was not talking about a Palestinian 
state but rather about a Jordanian-Palestinian confederation, 
'Arafat was referring to a confederation between two states. 
This is the best practical solution for us, al-Husayni 
explained, because we want a Palestinian state. 
  Al-Husayni told Qol Yisra'el that a confederation agreement 
with Jordan would be possible only after the Palestinians and 
the Jordanians approved it in a national referendum. 

</TEXT>

