<H3> <TI>   PLO Survives `Financial Crisis,' Gets $29 Million </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0202082294 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 2 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0202082294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman--SAWT AL-SHA'B has learned that the PLO has 
survived the financial crisis that has plagued it over the past 
three years as a result of the position it took on the second 
Gulf war. 
  The PLO has received $29 million over the past few days. The 
following is a breakdown of the amounts received: 
  Greece provided $15 million, Turkey $2 million, Malaysia $5 
million, Indonesia $3 million, Algeria $2 million, not to 
mention the 8 million Saudi riyals transferred by the Saudi 
Popular Committee. 

</TEXT>

