<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mubarak, Delegation Return From Visit to Turkey </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0102195194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1905 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0102195194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Feb (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak and the 
delegation accompanying him returned safely to Cairo this 
evening, following a one-day visit to Turkey at the invitation 
of Turkish President Suleyman Demirel. 
  During the visit, President Mubarak held a series of 
intensive talks and important political meetings with the 
Turkish president, Prime Minister Tansu Ciller, Foreign Minister 
Hikmet Cetin, and a number of political and party figures. The 
purpose of the talks was to bolster ties of cooperation in the 
political, economic, trade, cultural, and media fields. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

