<H3> <TI>   Taxes To Be Collected for Palestinian Authority </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0202071294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 2 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0202071294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Palestinian authority in the Gaza Strip and 
Jericho will receive $170 million annually from taxes collected 
by Israeli Government bodies. Ya'ir Fidel, our economic 
correspondent in Tel Aviv, was apprised of this fact by a 
business source connected to the political process. This sum 
will furnish one-third of the Palestinian authority's budget. 
The source of the money will be port taxes, fuel surcharges, 
other taxes, and national insurance dues, which will be 
collected for the Palestinians by Israel. 

</TEXT>

