<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion Near Defense Ministry Wounds 2 Guards </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0202154894 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0202154894 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An explosive charge went off outside the Defense 
Ministry building in Baghdad last week. The explosion of the 
device that was hidden in a garbage container wounded two guards 
and caused material damage. 
  Reporting this, our sources said that a meeting of senior 
military officials of tyrant Saddam's regime was scheduled for 
that day, but the explosion caused chaos and forced the 
officials to postpone the meeting. No party has claimed 
responsibility but reports indicate that the explosion is part 
of some settling of accounts among Ba'thist regime members. 

</TEXT>

