<H3> <TI>   Commander Urges Army To Raise Preparedness Level </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0102180294 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 1 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0102180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Army Commander General Emile Lahhud has warned that 
Israel might escalate its aggression on the south because of 
what he called differences among Israeli officials on withdrawal 
from the occupied Arab territories. 
  In his monthly interview with the AL-JAYSH [Army] magazine, 
Lahhud called on the Army to raise the level of its preparedness 
to prevent Israel from using the south and local security 
incidents to its advantage during peace negotiations. 
  He stressed that only just and comprehensive solutions can 
bring about the kind of peace that protects dignity. He 
remarked that solidarity between Lebanon and Syria is the 
backbone of domestic stability. 
  Lahhud added that the Army has recently apprehended all 
violators in the north and south and that investigations into 
the Phalangist Party headquarters explosion have reached a 
serious stage. 

</TEXT>

