<H3> <TI>   Cyprus Minister Signs Communications Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3101221794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 31 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3101221794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Cypriot Minister of Communications and Works 
Adhamos Adhamidhis left Beirut for Larnaca this afternoon after 
a three-day visit to Lebanon during which he held talks with his 
Lebanese counterpart Muhammad Ghaziri. 
  A technical cooperation and coordination accord between the 
two countries was signed. It aims to promote Lebanese-Cypriot 
relations in posts and communications and the services linked to 
them. 
  Minister Ghaziri announced the formation of a technical 
committee comprised of Lebanese and Cypriots to draft an 
agreement on laying an undersea communications axial fiber cable 
between the two countries. He added that efforts are under way 
to extend an undersea cable with a capacity of 8000 axial lines. 
The first phase will begin with 4000 lines, of which Syria will 
have 16 percent with the remainder shared equally between 
Lebanon and Cyprus. [passage omitted] 
  The Cypriot minister, who also called on Foreign Minister 
Faris Buwayz, said the ongoing negotiations mark the start of 
important cooperation to develop ties between the two countries. 
He hoped that the accord will be a prelude to the continuation 
of good contacts between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

