<H3> <TI>   Brown Visit Said To Prompt Change in Boycott Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0102201494 Dubayy AL-BAYAN in Arabic 30 Jan 94 p 15 </F>
<F P=103> JN0102201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Dubayy AL-BAYAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Doha-QNA--Press reports said yesterday that the 
Jordanian Government has made an initial decision to abrogate 
the secondary and tertiary boycott of Israel, and that it is 
waiting for the Arab League decision on ending the primary 
boycott. 
  Quoting official Jordanian sources, newspaper AL-SHARQ said 
the new official Jordanian move has come following the recent 
visit to Amman by U.S. Commerce Secretary Ronald Brown, during 
which he demanded ending the secondary and tertiary boycotts of 
Israel that restrict U.S. companies' activities in the Middle 
East. 

