<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Alleges Sharif Received Aid From Israel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3001161694 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3001161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khalid Ahmad Kharal, the federal minister for 
information and broadcasting, said that during the rule of the 
Islamic Democratic Alliance and its mentor and patron, General 
Zia al-Haq, local bodies were misused for personal 
aggrandizement of the ruling alliance leaders. He was 
commenting on the statement by the opposition leader, in which 
he had criticized the dissolution of local bodies. He said 
during the 1988 and 1990 elections, the funds for local bodies 
were used to run the election campaigns of the Muslim League and 
its allied parties. On both the occasions, Pakistan Muslim 
League-Nawaz group used local bodies' funds for personal 
purposes, which forced the caretaker government to dissolve the 
local councils before the 1990 elections in order to ensure free 
and fair elections were conducted. 
  The information and broadcasting minister said that Mian 
Nawaz Sharif also received substantial assistance from Israel to 
destabilize the then government. The assistance was provided in 
the form of steel scraps through Israeli agents either free or 
at a nominal price. An Israeli ship named (Jamatul) delivered 
27,500 tons of scrap worth 240 million rupees. 

</TEXT>

