<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Sends Message to Russian Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0302071394 Paris AFP in English 0048 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0302071394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, Feb 3 (AFP) -- Palestine Liberation 
Organisation (PLO) leader Yasir 'Arafat sent a message to the 
Russian government Wednesday [2 February] to brief them on last 
weekend's peace talks with Israel in the Swiss resort of Davos, 
the Palestinian news agency WAFA reported. 
  'Arafat sent the message through Russia's ambassador to 
Tunis 
Boris Shchiborin after a meeting Wednesday at PLO headquarters 
here. 
  'Arafat is to meet Israel's chief negotiator Foreign 
Minister 
Shim'on Peres in Cairo next Monday in a bid to nail down a long 
overdue accord on withdrawing Israeli troops from the Gaza Strip 
and Jericho, territories earmarked for Palestinian autonomy 
under an historic accord signed on September 13. 
  The troops were supposed to have started pulling out on 
December 13, and their withdrawal is scheduled to be complete by 
April 13. 

</TEXT>

