<H3> <TI>   Judo Federation Official, Party Member Killed 2 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202232794 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202232794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Youth and Sports and all the 
administrators of the national movement for youth and sports 
announced today with great sorrow and deep regret the 
assassination this morning of Mr. Yahia Bouguetaya, deputy 
chairman of the Algerian Judo Federation and chairman of Mascara 
sports club. The Ministry calls on all officials and organizers 
of sports events throughout the national territory to mark one 
minute of silence on Thursday and Friday. 
  The Ettahaddi party announced today that a party member was 
killed in Constantine. The same source added that Mr Touali 
Mohamed who was 32-years old was kidnapped from his home last 
night before he was found assassinated with a sharp weapon. 

