<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liaison Secretary Meets OAU Head; Events Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202152094 Tripoli Great Jamahiriyah Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli Great Jamahiriyah Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The secretary of the General People's Committee of 
Foreign Liaison and International Cooperation yesterday met Dr. 
Salim Ahmed Salim, the secretary-general of the OAU, in Addis 
Ababa. The two sides discussed the crisis between the Great 
Jamahiriyah and the West in light of the African position of 
support for the Great Jamahiriyah, and examined ways to develop 
this position. 
  The two sides also discussed a number of issues concerning 
the African continent. During this meeting, the OAU secretary 
general stressed the importance of the role played by the Great 
Jamahiriyah in strengthening the freedom of the African 
continent. 
  The secretary of the General People's Committee of Foreign 
Liaison and International Cooperation also met in Addis Ababa 
yesterday afternoon the Sudanese foreign minister, the heads of 
the Tunisian, Mauritanian, and Algerian delegations and the 
assistant secretary-general of the Arab League who are all 
attending the 59th session of the OAU's Council of Ministers. 
During this meeting, the so-called Lockerbie affair was 
discussed, in addition to the agenda of the session, some 
African issues and Arab-African cooperation. 

</TEXT>

