<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Discusses Southern Issues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0202201994 Omdurman National Unity Radio in Arabic 1315 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0202201994 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman National Unity Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Husayn Sulayman Abu-Salih has again 
expressed Sudan's keenness and desire for the efforts of the 
Intergovernmental Authority on Drought and Development [IGADD] 
states initiative to produce the expected results in achieving 
peace. This was stated during separate meetings with the 
foreign ministers of Kenya and Uganda on the sidelines of the 
meetings of the ministerial council of the OAU in Addis Ababa. 
  Dr. Abu-Salih explained that during his meetings with the 
two 
ministers, he declared Sudan's interest in working to speed up 
steps to reach a comprehensive and acceptable solution that 
guarantees complete stability in the country. He said such a 
solution should end the dispute and its consequences. He added 
that the two ministers expressed their understanding of the 
Sudanese Government's stand and its seriousness in striving to 
find a peaceful solution to the dispute in the south. They also 
expressed their appreciation for the praise for the efforts of 
the IGADD states in this respect. 

</TEXT>

