<H3> <TI>   Seven Held for Questioning </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0202185494 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 2 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0202185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Randah Habib dispatch from Amman] </F>
  [Text] Jordanian Interior Minister Salamah Hammad has told 
us that seven people were arrested yesterday for interrogation 
in connection with the bomb blast at an al-Zarqa' cinema house. 
The minister did not elaborate. However, an official Jordanian 
source said that four of the arrested people are charged with 
last Thursday's blast in Amman and that the other three are 
suspected of having a connecttion with the bomb attack in 
al-Zarqa yesterday. 
  The source said that those arrested belong to groups of 
returnees from Afghanistan, adding that the explosive material, 
Acetone Peroxide, was used in both blasts but said that the 
explosives were prepared in a very crude manner which means that 
the group did not have enough experience in such explosions. 
  The two explosions this week resulted in the injury of nine 
people, two seriously. 

</TEXT>

