<F P=102>  JN0102132594 Amman Radio Jordan in English 1200 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0102132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Chinese delegation has arrived in Amman for trade 
talks on bolstering commercial exchanges between the two 
countries. The delegation, led by deputy chief of the Chinese 
Council for International Trade Development, Ye Peng, will meet 
private and public sector economists. 
  The trade balance between the two countries is still in 
China's favor. Jordan's imports of Chinese goods surged from 
$29 million in 1991 to $53 million in 1992. Jordanian exports 
to China, mainly potash, rose from $18 million in 1990 to 32.5 
million dinars [as heard] in 1991. 

</TEXT>

