<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sources See `Test' Facing Rabin Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0202105694 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 1 Feb 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM0202105694 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Salwa al-Ustuwani report: "Syria Accuses Israel of </F>
Obstructing Peace"] 
  [Excerpt] Damascus -- Syria yesterday accused Israel of 
continuing to adhere to its method, obstructing any tangible 
progress in the peace process. Authoritative Syrian sources 
told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that the Washington negotiations have so 
far inspired no hope of achieving success in the peace process. 
And that the Israeli delegation continues to avoid providing 
clear and frank answers with regard to the issue of complete 
withdrawal from the Golan and the occupied Arab territories, 
which is the basis for a just and comprehensive peace. 
  The sources added that the round to be held between the 
Syrian and Israeli delegations will be crucial in determining 
the fate and future of the negotiation process, especially as 
the United States has decided to assume the task of imparting 
the necessary impetus to the political peace process on all 
tracks and renewed before the world in Geneva its commitment to 
achieving a just and comprehensive peace on all fronts. 
  The sources went on: Thus Rabin and his government will be 
subjected to a test with regard to their willingness to respond 
to the will of the international community and Washington. 
  The Syrian sources urged the international community to 
shoulder the responsibility for salvaging and implementing its 
legitimacy and putting an end to Israeli evasion. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

