<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Special Commission Talks Begin in Baghdad </TI></H3>
<H4>   Delegations Open Official Talks </H4>
<F P=102> JN0202192094 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1855 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0202192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 2 Feb (INA)--Official talks between Iraq 
and the UN Special Commission began here this evening. 
  The Iraqi delegation to the talks is led by Foreign Minister 
Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf. The Special Commission's delegation 
is led by its chairman, Rolf Ekeus. 
  On the Iraqi side are Lieutenant General 'Amir Muhammad 
Rashid, director of the Military Industrialization Organization; 
Dr. Riyad al-Qaysi, Foreign Ministry under secretary; and a 
number of officials. On the Special Commission's delegation are 
Maurizio Zifferero, deputy chairman of the International Atomic 
Energy Agency, Tim Terevan [name as received], the committee 
spokesman; and John Scott, the committee's legal adviser. 
  Ekeus and the accompanying delegation arrived in Baghdad at 
noon today on a visit of several days to Iraq. 

</TEXT>

