<F P=102> JN0302095694 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0915 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0302095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 3 Feb (INA)--Iraq and the UN Special 
Commission held a second round of talks at the Foreign Ministry 
this morning. 
  The Iraqi side to the talks was led by Foreign Minister 
Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf. Rolf Ekeus, chairman of the UN 
Special Commission, led the Commission's side to the talks. 
  The Iraqi side comprised Lieutenant General 'Amir Muhammad 
Rashid, director of the Military Industrialization Organization; 
Dr. Riyad al-Qaysi, Foreign Ministry under secretary; and 
several Foreign Ministry officials. The Special Commission's 
side comprised Zifferero, deputy chairman of the International 
Atomic Energy Agency, John Scott, the Commission's legal 
adviser; and Tim Terevan [name as received], official spokesman 
for the Commission. 

