<H3> <TI>   UN Special Commission Talks Begin in Baghdad </TI></H3>
<H4>   Ekeus Comments on Second Round Talks </H4>
<F P=102> JN0302111994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1047 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0302111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 3 Feb (INA)--A second round of talks 
lasting two and half hours between Iraq and the UN Special 
Commission held at the Foreign Ministry was concluded at noon 
today. 
  In a statement to the IRAQI NEWS AGENCY after this round of 
talks, Rolf Ekeus said: "We are continuing our talks on future 
steps. I cannot elaborate any further on the issue, since the 
talks are continuing. We are holding working sessions." 
  Ekeus spoke to reporters on his arrival at the al-Rashid 
Hotel, where he is staying, expressing hope that progress will 
be made. He added: I am convinced that we will make progress. 
We will continue our discussions tomorrow. It is premature to 
provide details about the talks. 
  The first round of talks between Iraq and the Special 
Commission was held here last night. 

</TEXT>

