<H3> <TI>   Saddam Orders Cash Awards for Car Thieves' Capture </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0202191094 Baghdad AL-JUMHURIYAH in Arabic 30 Jan 94 p1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0202191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-JUMHURIYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Latif al-Tayyib] </F>
  [Text] Baghdad--Leader President Saddam Husayn, may God 
preserve him, has ordered a 30,000-dinar award for whoever 
captures a car thief. A responsible source at the Interior 
Ministry told AL-JUMHURIYAH that the president's order covers 
citizens, party organizations, and Internal Security Forces 
personnel who capture car thieves. The source urged police 
departments and party organizations to submit the names of those 
entitled to the award to the Presidential Council after the 
crime of car theft is legally proved. He stressed that this 
noble gesture will effectively contribute toward curbing the 
phenomenon of car theft. He said the award provides an 
incentive for the Internal Security Forces personnel to do 
everything possible to remove this phenomenon. 

</TEXT>

