<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Escort Said Dead After Alleged Attempt on Saddam </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0202134294 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 1 Feb 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM0202134294 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Iraqi Opposition Talks of Attempt To </F>
Kill Saddam"] 
  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Iraqis arriving in 
Amman from Baghdad the night before last have claimed that one 
of President Saddam Husayn's escorts tried to open fire on the 
president but the other escorts killed the escort with a hail of 
machinegun bullets. 
  The Iraqis said that the dead escort, who held the rank of 
captain, came from Tikrit, Saddam's birthplace. 
  The Iraqi president (last summer) himself shot and killed 
his 
escort Mu'ayyad al-'Ayyash because he had informed an Iraqi 
family of a secret place in southern Baghdad in which Saddam was 
present. Al-'Ayyash, too, came from Tikrit and had family ties 
with the president. 
  The Iraqis who spoke about the new attempt believe that it 
occurred less than a month ago just outside Baghdad and that a 
quick reshuffle was made immediately in the protection teams 
assigned to guard the Iraqi president. 
  The most recent report leaked from Baghdad spoke about the 
blowing up of an agricultural tractor on a road through which 
the Iraqi president's motorcade passed on its way to one of his 
bunkers outside the capital. At the time suspicion revolved 
around the president's escorts and senior leaders, who were the 
only ones who had known that the president's motorcade would use 
this country road. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

