<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Inaugurates Refrigeration Compressor Plant </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0202204594 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1700 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0202204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Staff General Husayn Kamil Hasan, minister of 
industry and minerals and supervisor of the Military 
Industrialization Organization [MIO], today inaugurated a plant 
for the production of compressors at the State Enterprise for 
Electrical Industries. The plant has an annual production 
capacity of 500,000 compressors. 
  As he toured the plant's sections, the minister was 
acquainted with the progress of the production operations. He 
gave instructions for increasing production to serve the 
manufacturing of locally-made freezers and refrigerators, of 
which compressors constitute a basic part. 
  Staff Gen. Husayn Kamil Hasan also inaugurated a 
comprehensive irrigation pumps fair at the State Enterprise for 
Mechanical Industries. During a conversation with workers at 
the enterprise, the minister said that the zealous personnel of 
the Ministry of Industry and Minerals, with the effective 
support of the MIO formations, are presenting this 
accomplishment as a gift to the leader of the march, leader 
President Saddam Husayn. He said that after the country's need 
for chemical and phosphatic fertilizers has been fully met in 
the service of the agricultural sector, this distinguished 
effort constitutes a new technological link in defiance of the 
circumstances of the unjust blockade. 
  An Iraqi News Agency correspondent said that the State 
Enterprise for Mechanical Industries has put into action its 
productive plan for this year. This plan aims at producing and 
manufacturing thousands of pumps of various sizes through 100 
percent Iraqi designs, molds, and technological methods. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

