<F P=102>  AU0302103494 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 3 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU0302103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Busek Inaugurates Professorship"] </F>
  [Text] Jerusalem -- On Wednesday [2 February], during his 
visit to Israel, Vice Chancellor Erhard Busek met with Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin for a talk and for the signing of a 
scientific-technological cooperation agreement. 
  As Vice Chancellor Busek stressed, during the meeting Rabin 
pointed out the "international responsibility for peace in the 
Middle East." The international community, which has called for 
peace for years, must now also participate in the reconstruction 
of the Palestinian territories. 
  In the afternoon Busek inaugurated the 
"Franz-Cardinal-Koenig 
Professorship for Austrian Studies" at the Hebrew University of 
Jerusalem. 
  Previously Busek was the first Austrian politician to lay a 
wreath at the grave of Theodor Herzl, the father of political 
Zionism, and visited the Yad Vashem memorial for the 6 million 
victims of the Holocaust. 

</TEXT>

