<H3> <TI>   U.S. Ambassador Delivers Message to Buwayz </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0202174394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0202174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz met U.S. Ambassador in 
Lebanon Mark Hambley this afternoon. They reviewed bilateral 
relations and the ongoing Washington talks. 
  Ambassador Hambley handed Minister Buwayz a written message 
from his U.S. counterpart Warren Christopher, the contents of 
which were not disclosed. The U.S. ambassador denied any 
knowledge of an imminent trip by Christopher to the region 
before the resumption of talks. He said that the approval of 
the appointment of Dr. Riyad Tabbarah as Lebanon's ambassador in 
Washington is being discussed by the two governments and that 
once the approval is given it will be made public at the proper 
time. 
  Minister Buwayz met today with Ambassador Tabbarah, who said 
that he will leave for Washington when he receives the U.S. 
Administration's approval. 

