<H3> <TI>   Khamene'i Rejects President's Amnesty Proposal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0202102094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 30 Jan 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PM0202102094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Khamene'i Rejects Rafsanjani Request </F>
To Issue Amnesty for Thousands of Iranian Prisoners"] 
  [Excerpt] Tehran, London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Iranian 
"Supreme Guide" 'Ali Khamene'i has rejected a request submitted 
by President Hashemi-Rafsanjani to issue a general amnesty for 
thousands of prisoners in Iran. 
  Sources close to the Rafsanjani wing have said that the 
Iranian president was hoping that the amnesty -- coupled with 
new measures to ease the restrictions imposed on cultural 
activities -- would help Iran to improve its image with regard 
to its human right records. But its seems that Khamene'i took 
the advice of hard-line factions opposed to any "sign of 
weakness." 
  Rafsanjani suffered another setback yesterday when the 
Majles 
Financial Committee announced its disapproval of the 
government's proposal to increase petrol prices from 250 riyals 
to 600 riyals -- an increase of 22 cents. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

