<H3> <TI>   Trilateral Border Security Meeting Begins in Islamabad </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202222094 Tehran IRNA in English 2140 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202222094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 2, IRNA -- Iran, Pakistan, Afghanistan 
opened a five-day trilateral meeting in Islamabad on Tuesday to 
consolidate cooperation on border security, the anti-drug 
headquarters at the president's office announced here Wednesday. 
  It said the ongoing meeting is being held at the proposal of 
the United Nations. An Iranian delegation is in Islamabad to 
attend the meeting. 
  The participants are studying the plan for strengthening 
border security cooperation. After the meeting the delegates 
are to visit the joint border areas and will later hold talks 
with Iran's Minister of the Interior 'Ali Mohammad Besharati in 
Tehran, it added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

