<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Minister Meets With Western Australian Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202212894 Tehran IRNA in English 2038 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202212894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 2, IRNA -- In a meeting here Wednesday 
with Deputy Prime Minister of Western Australia Hendy Kuan, 
Iran's deputy foreign minister for Asia-Pacific affairs, 
Allaeddin Borujerdi, said Iran was ready to export nonoil 
products to Australia. 
  He said Iran looks forward to balanced trade reltions with 
Australia. 
  The visiting Australian official said his country would 
exert 
efforts for ensuring balanced trade ties with Iran. 
  He also expressed hope that relations between Iran and 
Australia would continuously develop. 

</TEXT>

