<F P=100> Morocco </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Deliver Message From King to Egypt's Mubarak </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102135794 Rabat MAP in English 1234 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat MAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, Feb 1 (MAP) -- Egyptian President Husni 
Mubarak Monday received a verbal message from King Hassan II. 
  The message was conveyed by Mohamed Aouad, adviser to the 
Moroccan king, who was accompanied by Moroccan Culture Minister 
Mohamed Allal Si Nasser. 
  Si Nasser at the end of the meeting told the press the 
Egyptian president voiced feelings of fraternity towards the 
Moroccan sovereign with whom he shares identical views on issues 
concerning the Arab world. 
  Talks covered the broadlines of the ongoing conference on 
Moroccan-Egyptian relations, Si Nasser said adding that 
President Mubarak who surveyed the development of the Middle 
East peace talks explained that problems accumulated for decades 
cannot be resolved in one or two phases of negotiations. 
  Aouad and Si Nasser arrived here Sunday to partake in the 
conference on Moroccan-Egyptian relations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

