<H3> <TI>   Embassy in Moscow Denies Report of Frozen PLO Funds </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0302143494 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 3 Feb 94 p5 </F>
<F P=103> PM0302143494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Kuwait Denies Freezing PLO Assets"] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, AL-HAYAH -- The Kuwaiti Embassy in Moscow 
has expressed "regret" at the report carried by the official 
news agency ITAR-TASS claiming that Kuwait had frozen the PLO's 
assets in Kuwait. A statement issued by the embassy said that 
the PLO had transferred tens of millions of dollars since July 
1991 from its accounts in Kuwait to Jordan and Switzerland 
without any Kuwaiti objection. 
  The statement emphasized that "the people and Government of 
the state of Kuwait adopt a principled stance in support of the 
Palestinian people's just cause and legitimate rights." 

</TEXT>

