<H3> <TI>   Arab League Offer To Host Accord Signing Declined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0302152094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1212 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0302152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Feb (MENA)--An Arab League official has 
emphasized the importance of achieving Yemeni reconciliation to 
strengthen Arab solidarity and the Arab nation's objectives. 
  The official made this statement while commenting on reports 
that the Yemeni leadership has refused the Arab League's offer 
to sign the document of "the Yemeni accord agreement" at the 
Arab League headquarters in Cairo and prefers to have it signed 
in the Jordanian capital of Amman. 
  The official said: The place where the document will be 
signed is not important. The important thing is to have 
reconciliation between the Yemeni leaders in the interest of 
that country's people. 
  Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid had 
telephoned Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and Vice 
President 'Ali Salim al-Bid offering to host the signing of the 
accord agreement between them. The Yemeni leadership declined 
the offer in favor of Amman, as Jordan's King Husayn was the 
mediator in the reconciliation between the Yemeni president and 
his deputy before the offer was made by the Arab League 
secretary general. 

</TEXT>

