<H3> <TI>   Delegates Conclude Negotiations in Washington </TI></H3>
<H4>   Buwayz: Talks To Resume 15 Feb </H4>
<F P=102> NC0302213794 Paris AFP in English 2103 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0302213794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, Feb 3 (AFP)--Arab-Israeli bilateral peace 
negotiations will resume February 15 in Washington at the 
delegates' level, Lebanese Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz said 
Thursday [3 February]. 
  The 12th session of the bilateral talks which began on 
January 24 ended Wednesday in Washington. 
  The negotiations were held at secret locations at the heads 
of delegations level between Israelis, Lebanese, Syrians, 
Jordanians and Palestinians. 

</TEXT>

