<H3> <TI>   Arab League Official on Lifting of Libya Sanctions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402093894 Tripoli JANA in English 0842 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli JANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Addis Ababa, Al Nowar [Feb] 4 -- JAMAHIRIYA NEWS 
AGENCY -- The assistant secretary general of the Arab League has 
called for the lifting of the harsh measures imposed on the 
Great Jamahiriyah by resolutions manipulated through the 
so-called `Security' Council. He said that the continuation of 
these sanctions would be a blatant injustice and a mockery of 
small nations, principles of international law and the United 
Nations Charter. 
  In a speech to the 59th session of ministers of the 
Organisation of African Unity in Addis Ababa, the assistant 
secretary general of the Arab League said that we call for all 
resolutions adopted by the Arab League, the Organisation for 
African Unity, the Islamic Conference Organisation and the 
Nonaligned Movement to be complied with. 

</TEXT>

