<H3> <TI>   Afghan Official Urges Iran To Send Refugees Help </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302155894 Tehran IRNA in English 1521 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 3, IRNA -- Heshmatollah Mujeddedi here 
today called on the Islamic Republic of Iran to send relief aid 
to Afghan refugees in southern deserts of Afghanistan. 
  Mujeddedi, who is here at the head of a delegation from 
Afghanistan's Supreme Islamic revolution Coordination Council, 
in a meeting with Deputy Foreign Minister for Asia-Pacific, 
Ala'ddin Borujerdi, expressed regrets over the ongoing clashes 
in Afghanistan. 
  He also thanked Iran for its efforts to end clashes in 
Afghanistan and urged the Iranian officials to continue their 
efforts to put an end to the hostilities. 
  Borujerdi said that as before Tehran would do all it can to 
provide the Afghan refugees with their requirements. 
  He expressed concern over the present situation in 
Afghanistan and said Iran would spare no efforts to help 
Afghanistan solve its problems. 

</TEXT>

