<H3> <TI>   PFLP-GC Cable Urges Continued Struggle </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0302191894 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0302191894 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Central Committee of the Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine-General Command [PFLP-GC] has sent a 
cable of greetings to the members of the Central Committee of 
the Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP], on 
the DFLP's 25th anniversary. 
  The cable says: To the dear comrades, you know these 
national occasions, in the book of national strugglers and 
revolutionaries of national liberation, provide a good 
opportunity for assessment of past achievements in their 
struggle. 
  This anniversary comes amid very complicated and difficult 
circumstances brought about by international, regional, Arab, 
and national developments fraught with dangers that target all 
of us, Arabs and Muslims. The results of these developments and 
the way we respond to them will determine the fate of our 
people's cause, their rights, and national existence, as well as 
the fate of the rights of Arabs and Muslims, their present, 
future, and national, regional, and human role. 
  The cable adds: Historic responsibility entails missions to 
be performed by all Arab and Islamic forces that are committed 
to the defense of inalienable, historic rights and that are 
aware of the comprehensive visible dangers. The purpose of this 
is to foil plans to recognize the Zionist enemy and normalize 
relations with it, support Palestinian national steadfastness in 
the face of the conspiracy, and emphasize the Arab and Islamic 
dimension of the cause and the conflict. We think that our 
present situation and national performance play a major role in 
the nation's awakening to assume its responsibilities. 

</TEXT>

