<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Briefs Russian Envoy on Davos Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302184594 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 3 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302184594 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Abu-Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], president of the 
state of Palestine and chairman of the PLO Executive Committee, 
last night received the Russian ambassador in Tunis who conveyed 
to him a message from the Russian leadership. 
  Brother President Abu-Ammar asked the ambassador to convey a 
message to the Russian leadership on the Israeli-Palestinian 
talks in Davos and Israel's attempts to delay implementation of 
the Declaration of Principles. 
  The meeting was also an opportunity to review the various 
stages of the peace process and the worsening situation in the 
occupied territories as a consequence of the occupation and 
Israel's violation of Palestinians' human rights. 

