<H3> <TI>   Assassination Plot Against 'Arafat in Amman Denied </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0302173094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 3 Feb 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM0302173094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Palestinian Official Denies Attempt </F>
To Assassinate 'Arafat by Shooting Down His Aircraft With 
Missile"] 
  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- An authoritative source 
at the Palestinian embassy in Amman yesterday denied reports of 
the uncovering of a plot to assassinate Palestinian President 
Yasir 'Arafat during his visit to Amman last month. 
  The source told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that these reports are 
absolutely baseless and unfounded. The source added that he had 
no information about reports that Jordanian security forces had 
arrested a Palestinian group armed with shoulder-mounted rockets 
prepared for launching in the direction of 'Arafat's aircraft as 
it landed in Amman civilian airport. 
  For their part, Jordanian security sources have declined to 
comment on the report, which was published by a local newspaper. 

</TEXT>

