<H3> <TI>   PRC Spokesman Comments on Border Talks in Delhi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0302160694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0302160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India and China today began discussions on reduction 
of troop levels on the line of actual control. The expert group 
set up to assist the joint working group of both the countries 
met in New Delhi and both sides reiterated their determination 
to successfully carry out the task. The group will formulate 
measures to implement the agreement on maintenance of peace and 
tranquillity along the line of actual control signed during the 
prime minister, Mr. Narasimha Rao's visit to China last 
September. 
  Meanwhile, in Beijing, the Chinese Foreign Ministry 
spokesman 
expressed the hope that the ongoing Sino-Indian expert group 
talks in New Delhi will mark a step forward in the settlement of 
the boundary issue. Responding to queries, the spokesman said 
the purpose of the talks is to implement the understanding and 
agreement reached between the two sides. He said there is 
tranquillity along the border and this fact is to the 
satisfaction of both China and India. 
  The leader of the Chinese delegation, Mr. Fu Xuezhang, 
called 
on the minister of state for external affairs, Mr. R.L. Bhatia. 
Mr. Fu informed the minister of the friendly atmosphere and the 
discussions in the experts group which met for the first time. 
Mr. Bhatia expressed the hope that the discussions will be 
successful. The group will continue its talks tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

