<H3> <TI>   Minister Urges Vigilance Along Bangladesh Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0402062294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0435 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0402062294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The union minister of state for home, Mr. Rajesh 
Pilot, has urged the security forces along the country's border 
with Bangladesh to be more alert. Addressing the personnel of 
the Assam Rifles in Shillong, he said insurgent activities of 
the region are on the increase during the past few months. 
Later, he met the Meghalaya chief minister, Mr. S.C. Marak, and 
senior state government officials. 
  Mr. Pilot, who is now on a visit to the northeastern region, 
told our correspondent that he will hold discussions with the 
state governments on matters relating to security and law and 
order. He said Pakistan is trying to make inroads in the region 
by aiding and abetting some insurgent groups through Bangladesh. 

</TEXT>

