<F P=102>  JN0402093094 Amman AL-RA'Y in Arabic 4 Feb 94 p 26 </F>
<F P=103> JN0402093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-RA'Y </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] AL-RA'Y has learned that the Embassy of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran in Amman intends to reduce the number of 
diplomats working in the embassy. 
  By the end of the month, 21 Iranian diplomats working in the 
Iranian Embassy are expected to leave Amman in response to a 
Jordanian Government request that the Iranian Government reduce 
the number of diplomats working in its mission in Jordan to a 
number equal to that of the staff of the Jordanian diplomatic 
mission in Tehran. 
  The Iranian Government responded favorably to the Jordanian 
Government's request to reduce the number of staff at its 
diplomatic mission in Jordan. 

