  [Excerpts] His Majesty the king visited Jordanian troops 
serving under the United Nations flag in Croatia. Upon arrival 
in Zagreb Airport, his majesty, the supreme commander of the 
Armed Forces, expressed hope for the return of peace in the 
former Yugoslavia. The king said the Jordanians were privileged 
in playing a peacekeeping role in that region: 
  [Begin recording] [Husayn] The purpose of my visit is, 
obviously, to have the chance to see Jordanians who've had the 
privilege to represent our country in the search for peace and 
security for our friends in this entire region. And it is 
certainly our hope that, before too long, we shall see things 
develop in that direction, God willing. 
