<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Air, Sea, Land Escalation Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0402123594 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1130 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0402123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Zionist enemy escalated its land, sea, and air 
aggression against Lebanon today. Enemy forces bombarded the 
western and central sectors of south Lebanon this morning. 
Israeli gunboats cruised off the Lebanese coast in south 
Lebanon and enemy helicopters strafed several areas. 
  At 1115 today a resistance group attacked Bra'shit and Bayt 
Yahun posts and reports say they scored direct hits on both 
posts. Zionist enemy forces bombarded Bra'shit, Tibnin, and 
Haddatha. More than 10 shells landed in Bra'shit. The 
townships of al-Mansuri, Majdal Zun, Buyut al-Sayyid, and Zibqin 
came under sporadic artillery barrage that continued until noon 
and caused heavy property damage. An Amal resistance group 
retaliated by attacking the Jisr al-Hamra' and claimed the 
destruction of a 12.7-mm machine-gun post. 
  According to later reports from Tyre, the Islamic Resistance 
attacked two enemy posts in al-Hamra' and Radar Hill this 
morning. During the attack, resistance men detonated explosive 
charges near enemy patrols in the two villages. Hostile 
helicopters strafed the towns of a-Mansuri and Buyut al-Sayyid 
along with hostile gunboats. Hostile warplanes flew several 
sorties over the south this morning. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

