<F P=102>  LD0402115494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Greek foreign minister has described the Islamic 
Republic of Iran as a very important regional power. Welcoming 
our country's foreign minister at Athens airport, Karolos 
Papoulias described Velayati's visit to Greece as important. He 
said that issues relating to the Middle East, the Mediterranean, 
Central Asia, and the Balkans will be discussed at their talks. 
  Velayati left Bucharest for Athens last night, at the end of 
his two-day visit to Romania. Before leaving Bucharest he 
separately met and conferred with the Romanian president and 
parliament speakers. During the meetings President Ion Iliescu 
and the speakers of the Romanian parliament expressed gladness 
about the failure of the attempt on President 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani's life. They stressed the importance of the 
expansion of Tehran-Bucharest ties. 
  According to an IRNA report Ion Iliescu reiterated the 
grounds for cooperation between the two countries and emphasized 
Iran's role in Central Asia and the Persian Gulf region. He 
invited Hashemi-Rafsanjani to pay a visit to Romania. 
  Also, at a news conference, Velayati expressed gladness 
about 
the visit. He said that during his meetings with Iliescu he had 
submitted a verbal message from Hashemi-Rafsanjani to him. 

</TEXT>

