<H3> <TI>   Armed Group Attacks Mosque in Omdurman </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-Qadhdhafi Sends Condolences </H4>
<F P=102> EA0602190894 Khartoum SUNA in Arabic 1515 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0602190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 6 Feb (SUNA) -- The Libyan leader, Colonel 
Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi, leader of the first of September 
revolution in the Jamahiriyah, has expressed his country's 
concern over the incident at the mosque at locality [al-harah] 
One in Omdurman's al-Thawrah quarter last Friday [4 February], 
when armed foreigners fired at worshippers in the mosque. 
  A responsible source at the Republican Palace said that 
al-Qadhdhafi had asked the Sudanese Embassy to convey his 
warmest condolences to the families of the victims of the 
incident. 

</TEXT>

