<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction Noted to Events in Bosnia-Herzegovina </TI></H3>
<H4>   Lawyers Union Denounce `Massacre' </H4>
<F P=102> NC0702140694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1335 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0702140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Feb (MENA)--The Secretariat General of the 
Arab Lawyers Union strongly denounced the barbaric massacre 
committed by the Serb forces against Bosnia's Muslims in 
Sarajevo. It stressed that the massacre was the logical result 
of Europe's failure and U.S. reluctance to fulfill commitments 
toward areas of conflict. 
  In a statement today, the union said the massacre is 
consistent with undeclared intentions that are devoted to the 
ethnic liquidation and cleansing about which some countries are 
keeping silent. It also perpetuates several violations 
perpetrated by the Serb forces against innocent citizens, which 
were also ignored by the decisionmakers in the new world order. 
  The statement added that the massacre, which took place at 
the same time as the meeting of the UN Human Rights Committee in 
Geneva, highlights the Serbs' complete disregard for 
international legitimacy and human rights. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

