<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction Noted to Events in Bosnia-Herzegovina </TI></H3>
<H4>   Daily Urges No `Spectators' </H4>
<F P=102> NC0702073194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0601 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0702073194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Feb (MENA)--The newspaper AL-AKHBAR wonders 
whether the United Nations has become an establishment that only 
follows the orders of the major Western countries. It asks if 
the UN Charter has been amended to bless aggression against 
nations and human rights violations and reward aggressors. 
  In its editorial today, the newspaper says that the United 
Nations, the Security Council, and the major powers are adopting 
an unbelievable position and that the massacres inflicted on the 
people of Bosnia-Herzegovina over the past two years reveal that 
the international organization established in 1945 to defend 
security and prevent aggression is now only a scarecrow, like 
that which farmers set up to scare off crows. 
  The paper urges the Islamic countries not to remain 
spectators to this tragedy. The blood of a Muslim nation is 
being shed and its territory has become a human slaughterhouse. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

